{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 783290, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gnoktish", "body": "uhhg, Kil'jaedan was Defeated in the Sunwell and how do you know his spell is too weak huh? it took people a hard time back then to kill him off when he was raidable. Archimonde is dead and his remains dangle on the World Tree, Kil'jaeden is locked inside the Sunwell. Who else can you possibly think that Varmathiras would summon? we have no idea what he's capable off with Putress on his side.", "date": "2009-07-20T00:47:53-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 797178, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "433056", "body": "Kil'jaeden was defeated at the Sunwell, true, but he was only sent back to the nether, it's still possible for him to enter the world of Azeroth, though not through the Sunwell. In fact, the power that was used to summon Kil'jaeden was only a fragment of the Sunwell's original power after it was used to resurrect Kel'thuzad and was destroyed by Arthas and the Scourge (Impressively Kael'thas found the girl in which the last power of the Sunwell was stored). \r\n\r\nSargeras on the other hand have been to Azeroth in his current shape. He was inside Medivh. Of course no one, except Blizzard, knows where he is now, but my guess is that it would be easier to get Sargeras to Azeroth than Kil'jaeden for the simple fact: Sargeras doesn't have a physical form any longer.", "date": "2009-08-03T16:47:26-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
