{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 400351, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "lifedragon", "body": "damn that looks wicked. i am really hoping thought they stop doing graphic upgrades or i am going to have to buy a new computer :(", "date": "2008-10-08T16:18:26-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "For wrath of the lich king, any mid-range computer will do fine. WoW is still in DX9, new games these days are in DX10 graphics.", "creationdate": "2008-10-14T19:15:19-05:00", "id": 50651, "rating": 7, "commentid": 400351, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Anarchy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "... except there's very little difference between DX9 and DX10. And WoW could very easily be MUCH more realistic-looking and draining if Blizzard wanted it to. But they want people to be able to play WoW without max spec machines, so they intentionally make graphics lighter.  (Though this does change over time, the graphics detail jump from 1.x to 2.x was quite steep.)  OH and new games these days aren't really DX10, since Microsoft made DX10 require Vista. (Not that it really does, it's been backported to XP by freelancers, but game producers can't assume that people run hackware.)", "creationdate": "2008-10-19T19:54:32-05:00", "id": 51547, "rating": 7, "commentid": 400351, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mikk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 419820, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "whitedragon254", "body": "I think theres actually a glitch with the model listing. it says varimathras' model is Mal'ganispurpleskin, yet his armor and basicly everything about him in his model is green. And Mal'ganis' skin is labeled Mal'ganisgreenskin, yet everything about him in his model is purple. Either its a glitch with wowhead or blizzard doesnt know the difference between green and purple.", "date": "2008-10-25T16:33:05-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 448905, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Acetylcholine", "body": "Can anyone confirm this for me?  After the Wrathgate quest is complete, Varimathras appears dead to you.  Does this mean you are unable to pick up and complete any of the quests he'd normally give you?  I'm interested because this might affect my Loremaster achievement.", "date": "2008-11-16T22:21:48-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That appears to be the case, I went back to Undercity after completing this and he is indeed gone for good. There doesn't appear to be any NPC there to replace him for quests either.", "creationdate": "2008-11-18T21:45:11-06:00", "id": 57307, "rating": 14, "commentid": 448905, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "31068", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed. It happened to me. I completed the Dragonblight quest chain for the battle of Undercity and then later went back to complete old-world quests. Any involving Varimathras, including turn-ins, are not possible.", "creationdate": "2009-01-01T10:03:31-06:00", "id": 376499, "rating": 0, "commentid": 448905, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rweagle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
